        <div class="row">

             <div class="col-md-3">
                <p class="lead">Ingredients</p>
                 <ul class="list-group">
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">1 bunch</span>
                    Kale
                  </li>
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">1 tbsp</span>
                    Seasoned salt
                  </li>
                  <li class="list-group-item">
                    <span class="badge">1 tbsp</span>
                    Olive oil
                  </li>
                                                                        
                </ul>

                <p class="lead">Additional Images</p>
                <a class="fancybox" rel="kale" href="<%= image_path('rawkale.jpg') %>" title="Uncooked kale">
                <%= image_tag "rawkale.jpg", :class => 'img-responsive image-spacing'%></a>
               
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-9">

                <div class="thumbnail">
                    <%= image_tag "kale.jpg", :class => 'img-responsive'%>
                    <div class="caption-full">
                        <h3 class = "header-spacing">Baked Kale Chips</h3>
                    </div>

                        <p class = "p-spacing">Research indicates that Kale is not only a very nutritious vegetable, but including it in your diet may help lower levels of bad cholesterol and reduce your risk of heart disease as well. The health benefits associated with kale include: blocking the growth of cancer cells, reducing the risks of coronary artery disease, and lowering levels of bad cholesterol.</p>

              </div>
              <div class = "thumbnail">
                    <div class="caption-full">
                        <h3>Preparation Instructions
                        </h3>
                        <em>Total Time: 25 minutes</em>
                    </div>

              <ol class = "preparation-instructions">
                   <li>Preheat an oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a non insulated cookie sheet with parchment paper.</li>                 
                  <li>
                  With a knife or kitchen shears carefully remove the leaves from the thick stems and tear into bite size pieces. Wash and thoroughly dry kale with a salad spinner. Drizzle kale with olive oil and sprinkle with seasoning salt.
                  </li>

                  <li>Bake until the edges brown but are not burnt, 10 to 15 minutes.</li>
                  
                </ol>

                </div>

